<field name="name">

&lt;P&gt;
B::Showlex - Show lexical variables used in functions or files

&lt;P&gt;
&lt;HR&gt;
</field>
<field name="synopsis">

&lt;P&gt;
&lt;PRE&gt;        perl -MO=Showlex&amp;#091;,SUBROUTINE&amp;#093; foo.pl
&lt;/PRE&gt;
&lt;P&gt;
&lt;HR&gt;
</field>
<field name="description">

&lt;P&gt;
When a subroutine name is provided in 
&lt;FONT SIZE=-1&gt;OPTIONS,&lt;/FONT&gt; prints the lexical variables used in that
subroutine. Otherwise, prints the file-scope lexicals in the file.

&lt;P&gt;
